"#feedbackModal_main_2526058\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bhq1665702755013.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bhq1665702755013.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bhq1665702755013.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bhq1665702755013\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Deploying Uniface Web Applications\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Uniface default installation includes a fully-configured Apache Tomcat HTTP Server and servlet engine for testing and deploying Uniface web applications. For production deployment, you can configure another web server and servlet engine to run Uniface applications after installation.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__context_w0ab1b5b1_w1ab1b5_w2ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__topic_d22847e1_d22848e1_d22849e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__p_d22850e1_d22851e1_d22852e1\">To deploy a Uniface web application, you need the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__li_d11183e1_d11184e1_d11185e1\">Web server capable of connecting to a servlet\n                  engine that is compliant with the 6.0 Jakarta servlet specification. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__li_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1\">Uniface Web Application Server, consisting of\n                  the Uniface Server, the Uniface Router, and the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher\n                  (WRD). </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__p_d22853e1_d22854e1_d22855e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dvq1665702540828.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dvq1665702540828.html\" title=\"A Uniface web application consists of one or more components that run in a Uniface Web Application Server and are accessed from a client browser via the HTTP or HTTPS protocol.\">How a Uniface Web Application Works</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__li_d11189e1_d11190e1_d11191e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Prepare the files and directories that need to be available in the web server. You can copy the resources or package them in a WAR file. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rsl1665702750327.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rsl1665702750327.html\" title=\"In a J2EE-compliant web server, deploy the web resources used by the Uniface web application.\">Deploying Web Application Resources</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__li_d11192e1_d11193e1_d11194e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure a web server and servlet engine to run the Uniface servlets. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mmb1665702745202.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mmb1665702745202.html\" title=\"Uniface automatically installs the Apache Tomcat Web Server, which is used for developing testing Uniface web applications and web services. In a production environment, you can use Tomcat as the web server for your deployed application, but you can use any Jakarta EE (Enterprise Edition) compliant web server with support for the Servlet 6.0 specification or higher.\">Configure a Web Server for Uniface Applications</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__li_d11195e1_d11196e1_d11197e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure the web deployment environment. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qsb1665702750396.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qsb1665702750396.html\" title=\"The Uniface Web Application Server (WASV) is automatically configured to work with the default Apache Tomcat web server, so you only need to perform this task if you are creating your own web deployment environment, or customizing the existing configuration.\">Configuring the Uniface Web Application Server</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__li_d11198e1_d11199e1_d11200e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Remove testing-related assignment settings and so on for a better performance. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ixo1665702755082.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ixo1665702755082.html\" title=\"Although Uniface applications are infrastructure independent at deployment, significant performance enhancements can be achieved by paying attention to the design of your applications, and the operation of your web server.\">Improving Performance of Web Applications</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__li_d11201e1_d11202e1_d11203e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, customize the error messages. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"egv1665702669743.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/egv1665702669743.html\" title=\"An error is displayed when a problem occurs in executing the desired Uniface service, for example, if an incorrect URL is provided.\">Web Application Error Pages</a>.\n            </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__result_w3ab1b5b5_w4ab1b5_w5ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__topic_d22856e1_d22857e1_d22858e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bhq1665702755013__p_d22859e1_d22860e1_d22861e1\">Depending on the purpose and audience of the application, you may need to select a domain name to serve as the address for your web site. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"txy1665702755162.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/txy1665702755162.html\" title=\"Domain names serve as the address for a Web site. Selecting and protecting your domain name is one of the most important issues in the creation of the your Web site.\">Obtaining a Domain Name</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tuz1665702667344.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Application Server</a><p>The Uniface Web Application Server (WASV) handles server-side processing for web and mobile applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ctl1665702541086.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Request Dispatcher (WRD)</a><p>The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) is used to deploy Uniface web applications. It is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering requests and maintaining connections between web servers and the Uniface Router. The WRD communicates with the Uniface Server via the Uniface Router.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526058\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526058\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Deploying Uniface Web Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Deploying Uniface Web Applications The Uniface default installation includes a fully-configured Apache Tomcat HTTP Server and servlet engine for testing and deploying Uniface web applications. For production deployment, you can configure another web server and servlet engine to run Uniface applications after installation. To deploy a Uniface web application, you need the following: Web server capable of connecting to a servlet engine that is compliant with the 6.0 Jakarta servlet specification. Uniface Web Application Server, consisting of the Uniface Server, the Uniface Router, and the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD). For more information, see How a Uniface Web Application Works . Prepare the files and directories that need to be available in the web server. You can copy the resources or package them in a WAR file. For more information, see Deploying Web Application Resources . Configure a web server and servlet engine to run the Uniface servlets. For more information, see Configure a Web Server for Uniface Applications . Configure the web deployment environment. For more information, see Configuring the Uniface Web Application Server . Remove testing-related assignment settings and so on for a better performance. For more information, see Improving Performance of Web Applications . Optionally, customize the error messages. For more information, see Web Application Error Pages . Depending on the purpose and audience of the application, you may need to select a domain name to serve as the address for your web site. For more information, see Obtaining a Domain Name . Related Links Web Application Server The Uniface Web Application Server (WASV) handles server-side processing for web and mobile applications. Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) is used to deploy Uniface web applications. It is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering requests and maintaining connections between web servers and the Uniface Router. The WRD communicates with the Uniface Server via the Uniface Router. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}